series_description: This series documents the tax implications pertaining to any funds distributed by the agency. This series may include, but is not limited to: tax forms, reports, correspondence, and project files.
retention_statement: 7 Years after end of state fiscal year

series_description: This series documents internal and external investment performance, asset balances, custodians of accounts, analysis, schedules of income and loss, actuarial analysis (pricing, tuition, and investment return assumptions), and reconciliations. This series may include, but is not limited to: statements, reports, and correspondence.

This series documents liability release statements required for participation in various agency programs or promotions. This series may include, but is not limited to forms, statements and correspondence.

This series documents the registration, renewal, and certification of patents, trademarks, service marks, case and copyrights. This series may include but is not limited to applications, certificates, and correspondence.

This series documents promotions (drawings, contests, sweepstakes and/or surveys) used to promote account growth; supporting advertisements, the procedures for entry and selection; and the witnessing of the procedures. This series include, but is not limited to: forms, audio/visual materials, correspondence, and reports.
retention_statement: 5 Years after end of state fiscal year

series_description: This series documents the signatory authorizations given to individuals handling agency contracts, agreements, and/or financial transactions. This series may include, but is not to: signature cards or forms.
